# Locked: production authentication

- **Do not** “simplify”, reorder, or add health-check workarounds to [`deploy/deploy.sh`](deploy/deploy.sh) unless the user explicitly asks. The orchestration is documented in [`docs/infra/AUTH_PRODUCTION_LOCKED.md`](docs/infra/AUTH_PRODUCTION_LOCKED.md).

- **Canonical anon for ERP builds:** [`deploy/write-erp-env-from-supabase-docker-env.sh`](deploy/write-erp-env-from-supabase-docker-env.sh) reads `ANON_KEY` from `/root/supabase/docker/.env` only. **Do not** reintroduce copying `VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` from `docker exec supabase-kong` into `.env.production` by default (causes drift vs Vite-inlined bundles).

- **JWT regeneration:** [`deploy/fix-supabase-storage-jwt.sh`](deploy/fix-supabase-storage-jwt.sh) updates Supabase docker `.env` only; it does **not** write `NEWPOSV3/.env.production`.

- **GoTrue / CORS:** [`deploy/fix-supabase-kong-domain.sh`](deploy/fix-supabase-kong-domain.sh) and [`deploy/add-kong-cors-erp-origin.sh`](deploy/add-kong-cors-erp-origin.sh) own host + CORS for `erp.dincouture.pk`.

- **Client:** [`src/lib/supabase.ts`](src/lib/supabase.ts) and [`erp-mobile-app/src/lib/supabase.ts`](erp-mobile-app/src/lib/supabase.ts) use same-origin production URLs; [`SupabaseContext.tsx`](src/app/context/SupabaseContext.tsx) has intentional `SecurityError` handling — do not remove without review.

If the user reports login failures, read `docs/infra/AUTH_PRODUCTION_LOCKED.md` first, then diagnose (key mismatch vs `public.users` vs network), then propose a **minimal** fix with explicit approval to change this pipeline.
